    "body": "<span class=\"solution-visible-txt\">All submissions for this problem are available.</span><p>\u00a0</p>\n<p>Rohit Sharma was going through his scorecard of the previous world cup matches. He has played a total of <b>N</b> matches and has scored <b>A<sub>1</sub>, A<sub>2</sub>, A<sub>3</sub>, ..., A<sub>N</sub></b> runs in the matches. During the selection process, Dhoni wants to know the average score of Rohit Sharma. So, Rohit Sharma calculates his average as follows:</p>\n<li>He picks a match <b>i</b> (other than the last match) and replaces the score of <b>A<sub>i</sub></b> and <b>A<sub>i+1</sub></b> matches with a single score of <b>A<sub>i</sub> - A<sub>i+1</sub></b> reducing the number of matches in scorecard by 1.</li>\n<li>He continues the above process in the newly formed scorecard till the size of scorecard becomes 1.</li>\n<p>Help Rohit to maximise his average score.</p>\n<p>\u00a0</p>\n<h3>Input</h3>\n<p>First line contains an integer <b>N</b>, denoting the number of world cup matches.</p>\n<p>Next line contains <b>N</b> space separated integers, <b>A<sub>1</sub>, A<sub>2</sub>, A<sub>3</sub>,..., A<sub>N</sub></b>.</p>\n<p>\u00a0</p>\n<h3>Output</h3>\n<p>Print a single line containing the maximum average score possible.</p>\n<p>\u00a0</p>\n<h3>Constraints</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><b>1</b> \u2264 <b>N</b> \u2264 <b>10^6</b></li>\n<li><b>1</b> \u2264 <b>A<sub>i</sub></b> \u2264 <b>10^9</b></li>\n</ul>\n<p>\u00a0</p>\n<h3>Example</h3>\n<pre><b>Input:</b>\n4\n1 5 2 3\n\n<b>Output:</b>\n1\n</pre><p>\u00a0</p>\n<h3>Explanation</h3>\n<p><b>Example case 1.</b></p>\n<p>Array: 1 5 2 3</p>\n<li>Step 1: 1 3 3 (taking 2nd and 3rd score)</li>\n<li>Step 2: 1 0 (taking 2nd and 3rd score)</li>\n<li>Step 3: 1</li>\n",
